- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper mentions Valiant's approach in designing a sequence of reductions of the problem to other problems in different spaces, which may involve information theory. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper mentions the complexity of the algorithm, which may involve numerical analysis techniques. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper deals with the approximation factor and error control of the algorithm, which may involve discrete mathematics techniques.
